Gossypium arboreum

   [6492.jpg]
    Authority   L.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Malvales:Malvaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names cotton tree
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 6492

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A much-branched shrub up to 2 m or more, or a
   sub-shrub with few branches, 50-140 cm heigh. USES It is cultivated for
   the production of cotton fibres for textiles. GROWING PERIOD Perennial
   or annual, growing 150-180 days per year. COMMON NAMES Tree cotton.
   FURTHER INF Tree cotton probably originated in southern Africa. In
   Africa, it can be found at elevations between sea level and 1600 m and
   in India between sea level and 1000 m. It is sensitive to high winds
   and heavy rains. Photosynthesis pathway C3 II.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Sims D (pers. comm.)
   Purseglove J 1974 pp 333-363 [TEMP, KTMP, LIG, PHO, RAIN, TEXT, FER]
   Kernick M 1961 pp 232
   Duke J 1975 pp 17 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Onwueme I 1991 pp 377-386 [RAIN, TEXT, PH]
   Hartmann T 1981 pp 525-530 [TEMP, LIG, DRA, FER, PHO, DEP, TEXT, PH,
   SAL]
   Rehm S 1991 pp 338-343 [TEMP, KTMP, PHO, LIG, RAIN, LIMIT, DEP, DRA,
   PH, SAL, FER]

